pc:TextEquiv.pc:Unicode: Ka - ty did - n't! Ka - ty did - n't!
1. Gen - tly, gen - tly lay her low,
Soft - ly, soft - ly press the sod;
2. Plant the ros - es on her tomb,
Let them bud and blossom there;
3. O'er her form the wil-lows weep,
Thro' the boughs the breez-es sigh :
4. Hush ! sweet mu - sic fills the air,
Sum - mer birds are sing-ing clear;
5. Gen - tly, gen - tly come a - way,
Soft - ly, soft - ly press the sod;
Si - lent from the churchyard go;
And the pine groves mur - mur deep,
Weep not as ye homeward stray,
